#1510 implements the functionality described in the issue description as well as https://github.com/containers/buildah/issues/765#issuecomment-482709421 by injecting proxy vars into the container if they are set for `buildah from` or `buildah bud`

@maxmeyer does this meet your need?

Nothing in #1510 attempts to change anything for push or pull

> apt doesn't care about the http_proxy-variable- it needs instead a specific configuration file where the proxy-information is stored. More information here: https://askubuntu.com/a/116136/884040

This configuration file is very specific to apt. One way to tackle it would be to copy the file (in the Dockerfile) or mount it `buildah bud --volume` into the container.

@rhatdan @TomSweeneyRedHat is there a way to specify a temporary mount? What I mean by that is that files in mounted volumes are committed to the image as well. But it may be desirable to not commit those when they're only used for building.
